
______________________
Install Julia
______________________

cd /work2/11139/ab77394/frontera 
wget https://julialang-s3.julialang.org/bin/linux/x64/1.11/julia-1.11.1-linux-x86_64.tar.gz t
ar -xvf julia-1.11.1-linux-x86_64.tar.gz export PATH=/work2/11139/ab77394/frontera/julia-1.11.1/bin:$PATH

*Can also add this to bashrc*

Reload Bash: “source ~/.bashrc”

Check if Julia is available globally: “which julia” “julia —version”

----------------------------
Step 3: Create Python 3.9 environment
----------------------------
conda create -n pyjulia_env python=3.9 -y 
conda activate pyjulia_env
----------------------------
Step 4: Install PyTorch with GPU
----------------------------
conda install pytorch torchvision torchaudio pytorch-cuda=11.8 -c pytorch -c nvidia -y
Optional CPU-only fallback:

Maybe don’t do this:
conda install pytorch torchvision torchaudio cpuonly -c pytorch -y
----------------------------
Step 5: Install PyJuliaapptainer shell --nv --bind $WORK/myproject:/workspace myjuliaimage.sif

----------------------------
pip install julia>=0.7.2

In python3:
Import julia
julia.install()
----------------------------
Step 6: Test Julia from Python
----------------------------
To test it works - New python3: 
from julia.api import Julia 
jl = Julia(compiled_modules=False)
from julia import Main 
Main.eval("1 + 1")
----------------------------
Step 7 (Optional): Save environment
----------------------------
conda env export > pyjulia_env.yaml
